<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/14082957b6aa05a48615fccd31f6e462.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 4 and A = 45 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.0</li><li>5.7</li><li>45.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({45}\right)}}}=\frac{{4}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{4}}{{\tan{{\left({45}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{4}\approx{4}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{4}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={16}+{16}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={32}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{32}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5.6568542494924}\approx{5.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{45}^{\circ}\approx{45}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

